docs {
  # Login + CSRF bootstrap (ARCHITECTURE.md §1.3, R5)

  Every Co-Pilot surface is session-authenticated and CSRF-protected. Run
  these two requests first, in order:

  1. **Login** — POSTs credentials to the host login handler. On success the
     server sets a fresh session cookie; Bruno's cookie jar carries it on
     every subsequent request in this run automatically.
  2. **Fetch CSRF Token** — GETs the chat page and scrapes the
     `csrf_token_form` hidden field into the `csrf_token` env var, which the
     `Chat turn` request then submits. The CSRF token is minted per-session
     server-side (CsrfUtils), so it MUST be fetched after login.
}
